This seasonal Spanish take on an old classic sees the traditional negroni upgraded by the use of sweet sherry and aged whisky. This is a wonderful, and super-easy, festive aperitivo, not least for its vibrant red colour. Serves 1 35ml good scotch (preferably one aged in a PX cask) – we use Glenfiddich 15yo20ml pedro ximénez20ml Campari 1 slice dried pear, to garnish Fill a rocks glass with ice cubes, add the whisky, PX and Campari, and stir for five seconds. Garnish with a slice of dried pear and serve. • José Pizarro, Pizarro Bermondsey, London SE1